Description: Rim sherd of Attic black-figured pottery closed vessel, possibly a hydria; underside glazed streaky black; on edge: frieze of vertical strokes; top, between black bands, three incised spoked rosettes with added red dots on petals and in centres of hearts.
Bibliographic references: Venit 1982 / Painted Pottery from the Greek Mainland found in Egypt, 640-450 BC (p. 294-5, no. B273)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.0108) (Phase 1)
